cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with recognizing semantic features in faces using deep learning, which is a combination of computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the effects of various factors and hyper-parameters of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also explores the effectiveness of the system to recognize various semantic features, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the generation of 3-D Active Appearance Models of faces from real-world 2-D images, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the relation between high-level concepts and low-level features, which can be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
